            "body": ">  doesn't respect `alias man='man -a'` either.\r\n\r\nAliases are a shell feature, so that's not surprising.\r\n\r\nWe could perhaps provide a way to override the `man` command + args. \r\n\r\nBut you can already load manpage content in any buffer and the `:set filetype=man`. Did you try that? (If there are problems with that, we should fix that instead of adding a bunch of options.)",
